### Implementation 1: Basic Linear Transformation

```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.linalg.inv(S) @ F @ P.T
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 2: Weighted Least Squares

```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.linalg.inv(R) @ F @ P.T
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

